init_text: Your entire life, you've been told you're deathly allergic to bees. You've always had people protecting you from them, be it your mother or a hired hand. Today, one slips through and lands on your shoulder. You hear a tiny voice say "Your Majesty, what are your orders?"

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You look down and see a tiny bee in a suit and tie.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You look at the bee and say "I'm allergic to bees."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The bee looks at you and says "I'm sorry, Your Majesty, but I'm afraid I must carry out my orders.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You look at the bee and say "What do you mean I'm not allergic to bees?

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The bee looks at you and says "You are the queen of bees, Your Majesty.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You had no memory of your life as a bee, and the family had no memory of ever having found you.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You ask the bee what you should do.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The bee says that you should return to the hive, and that you will be welcomed with open arms.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You ask the bee if you can stay the way you are.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The bee says that the queen of bees can never be anything but a bee.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You could go on living your life as a human, and no one would be the wiser.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You look at him and think "That was easy."
